[{"id":"VR680433","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR680431.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following is a correct claim about the comet-star system as the comet moves along its orbit from distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 2\"><math alttext=\"r sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> to distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 1\"><math alttext=\"r sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the star?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR680433_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<html><body><div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the elliptical orbit of a comet about a star. The star is located about one-fourth of the way along the major axis of the ellipse. The shortest distance between the star and the comet in its orbit is labeled r sub 1. The longest distance between the star and the comet in its orbit is labeled r sub 2.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR680431.g02.svg\"/></div><p class=\"passage_para\">A comet of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub c equals, 3.2 times 10 to the 14 power kilograms\"><math alttext=\"m sub c equals, 3.2 times 10 to the 14 power kilograms\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3.2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>14</mn></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>kg</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> is orbiting a star with mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub s equals, 1.8 times 10 to the 30 power kilograms\"><math alttext=\"m sub s equals, 1.8 times 10 to the 30 power kilograms\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1.8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>30</mn></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>kg</mi></math></span></span>. The comet’s orbit is elliptical. At its closest point, the comet is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 1 equals, 8.3 times 10 to the 10 power meters\"><math alttext=\"r sub 1 equals, 8.3 times 10 to the 10 power meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8.3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>10</mn></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> from the star, and at its farthest point, the comet is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 2 equals, 4.9 times 10 to the 11 power meters\"><math alttext=\"r sub 2 equals, 4.9 times 10 to the 11 power meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4.9</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p></div></div></div></body></html>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the comet’s angular momentum increases.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The centripetal acceleration of the comet stays constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The work done by the star on the comet increases the total energy of the comet-star system.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the gravitational potential energy of the comet-star system will never be zero.</p>"],"answer":3}]